--- @meta
--- The damage event triggers before an actor is damaged. The damage value can be modified, or the damage can be prevented completely by blocking the event.
---
--- [Examples available in online documentation](https://mwse.github.io/MWSE/events/damage).
--- @class damageEventData
--- @field block boolean If set to `true`, vanilla logic will be suppressed. Returning `false` will set this to `true`.
--- @field claim boolean If set to `true`, any lower-priority event callbacks will be skipped. Returning `false` will set this to `true`.
--- @field activeMagicEffect tes3activeMagicEffect *Read-only*. Only valid for elemental shield reactive damage. It is the magic effect of the shield which will cause damage. Can be `nil`.
--- @field attacker tes3mobileCreature|tes3mobileNPC|tes3mobilePlayer *Read-only*. The mobile actor dealing the damage. Can be `nil`.
--- @field attackerReference tes3reference *Read-only*. The attacker mobile's associated reference. Can be `nil`.
--- @field damage number The amount of damage done.
