--- @field magicEffectIndex number *Read-only*. The index of the effect in source's effects list. Only valid if magicSourceInstance is set.
--- @field magicEffectInstance tes3magicEffectInstance *Read-only*. An instance of the magic effect in the spell that will cause the damage. Can be `nil`.
--- @field magicSourceInstance tes3magicSourceInstance *Read-only*. A `tes3magicSourceInstance` object of a spell that will cause the damage. Can be `nil`.
--- @field mobile tes3mobileCreature|tes3mobileNPC|tes3mobilePlayer *Read-only*. The mobile actor that is taking damage.
--- @field projectile tes3mobileProjectile|tes3mobileSpellProjectile *Read-only*. Projectile that will deal the damage. Can be `nil`.
--- @field reference tes3reference *Read-only*. The mobileâ€™s associated reference.
--- @field source tes3.damageSource *Read-only*. The origin of damage. These damage sources are present as [`tes3.damageSource`](https://mwse.github.io/MWSE/references/damage-sources/) constants. See the example. Damage with `tes3.damageSource.shield` source comes from magic shields. Other sources are self-explanatory.
